Brian Onyango of Mamelodi Sundowns clears ball from Eva Nga Bievenu of Chippa United. BackpagePix/Muzi Ntombela JOHANNESBURG - Mamelodi Sundowns returned to the DStv Premiership with a win over 10-men Chippa United to stretch their lead to 17 points at the top of the table. The Brazilians made a comfortable start at the Loftus Stadium. This after the visitors’ Siphesihle Mkhize was given his marching orders in the 24th minute for a studs-up challenge on Thabiso Kutumela. The hosts took the lead heading into half-time, courtesy of Andile Jali. He netted with a deflected shot and the score read 1-0 at the break. Substitute Teboho Mokoena made an impressive debut in his Brazilians jersey. He sealed a 2-0 win in the 87th minute, netting his first goal for Masandawana. Meanwhile, the Chilli Boys remain 12th on the log, just three points above the relegation zone.